snippet.title: Conor McGregor Dismissed Las Vegas Assault Deposition
snippet.description:
n his emergency motion to compel, Pegg says the fighter has delayed the depo since September 2017. He explains the deadline to have it done is in October but McGregor refuses to give him available dates. Pegg says McGregor’s deposition was scheduled for April 6, 2018, but “McGregor did not appear for his deposition. Instead, on the night of April 5, 2018, he was throwing metal barriers and other objects at the UFC 223, at which he was not scheduled to appear.”
...He accuses the fighter of delaying the depo for months and is demanding the judge order the fighter to sit and be grilled about the case.This type of disrespect toward the Legal Sustem ... Conor McGregor is going to Prison .
